  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Real-Time Monitoring of Gender-Based Violence Threats for Displaced Venezuelan Women and Girls in Ecuador, Brazil and Peru</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims at better understanding the patterns and drivers of certain forms of gender based violence (GBV), particularly sexual exploitation, for Venezuelan women/girls, and, most importantly, to improve protection strategies to prevent GBV and adapt GBV services to better meet survivors needs in the framework of the Venezuela response. It seeks to transform the regional GBV response by understanding &#x201C;survival sex&#x201D; and leveraging that knowledge to inform programming that addresses its underlying drivers. This project envisages the development of 3,000 displaced Venezuelan women/girls across three countries: Ecuador, Peru, and Brazil on their experiences with GBV and accessing resources. The data will be available for real-time analysis, having a transformational impact on the GBV response by informing protection interventions based on participatory, contextual, up to date data and providing services to better meet the needs of GBV survivors.</narrative>
  </description>
